name: Aztec Print Heart Shape Creole Earrings
description:
These earrings are a firm favourite of IRONIC FASHION; it's all about Creole. Add a little bit of Aztec decoration and you've got yourself a party for your earlobes.

Also, I'm not gon' sell you no nasty-ass, already worn earrings! Hell no, we got more than one pair of deez!

name: Wooden Cross Multi Chain Necklace
description:
Remember when Rosary beads were massive in about 2004? 

Remember when The Situation wore Rosary Beads throughout Series 1, 2 and 3 of Jersey Shore? 

Yeah, these aren't Rosary Beads. 

There's about five thin chains to this necklace, and the main feature of it is a black wooden Cross which sits just between your boobs. 

Does that count as blasphemy?

name: Leopard Print Square Creole Earrings
description:
These earrings way a tonne, but damn do they look good. 

Not much else to say about that really is there? 

Also, the metal looks kinda black, but it's not our fault; they came like that. They're sterilised; believe. 

P.S - I'm not gon' sell you no nasty-ass, already worn earrings! Hell no, we got more than one pair of deez!

name: Rose Bud Clip Ons
description:
Now these really are pretty lovely. If Lady Di wore plastic clip-on earrings, I'm pretty sure she'd wear these. 

Girl, imagine wearing these with your long ombre-d hair, with the colour on the roses popping out when the wind blows.

Cute, right?

name: Ornate Wreath Clip On Earrings
description:
These earrings are like the plastic 70s version of the metal Creoles I bang on about. 

We got them in black and yellow and the black ones are probably my favourite, and I know, I know, I shouldn't say that, but it's true. 

Saying that, the yellow ones would look pretty dope with a plain, sheer, turquoise silk t-shirt.

You know, for colour blocking n' all that.
